.TH "snd_hdac_sync_power_state" 9 "snd_hdac_sync_power_state" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hdac_sync_power_state \- wait until actual power state matches with the target state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" snd_hdac_sync_power_state
.BI "(struct hdac_device *codec "  ","
.BI "hda_nid_t nid "  ","
.BI "unsigned int power_state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "codec" 12
the HDAC device
.IP "nid" 12
NID to send the command
.IP "power_state" 12
target power state to wait for
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return power state or PS_ERROR if codec rejects GET verb.
